{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf3cb1412-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s162"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"162"},"text":"§ 162.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Description, claim","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No plant patent shall be declared invalid for noncompliance with section 112 if the description is as complete as is reasonably possible.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The claim in the specification shall be in formal terms to the plant shown and described.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf3cb1413-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950"},"text":"July 19, 1952, ch. 950","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/804"},"text":"66 Stat. 804","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s20/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 20(j)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/335"},"text":"125 Stat. 335","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf3cb1414-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf3cb1415-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 33, part (R.S. 4888, amended (1) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1915-03-03/ch94/s1"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1915, ch. 94, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/958"},"text":"38 Stat. 958","children":[],"tail":", (2) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-05-23/ch312/s2"},"text":"May 23, 1930, ch. 312, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/376"},"text":"46 Stat. 376","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The first paragraph is the provision in R.S. 4888 (see section 112). The second paragraph is not in the statute but represents the actual practice.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf3cb1416-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3cb1417-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" struck out “of this title” after “112”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf3cb1418-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3cb1419-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2011 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" effective upon the expiration of the 1-year period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"}